sentences: Zoran Janjetov (Serbian Cyrillic: Зоран Јањетов; born 23 June 1961) is a Serbian comics artist.
From 1981 to 1995, Janjetov worked on the Bernard Panasonik, published in magazines Yu strip magazin and Vreme zabave.
In 1986, Janjetov was chosen by Alejandro Jodorowski to finish the colour art in The Incal.
In 1983, Janjetov became a vocalist for the art rock band Heroina.
section: == Biography == | === Musical career and cover design ===

sentences: With the band he recorded one self-titled album, produced by Mitar Subotić and released in 1985.
section: == Biography == | === Musical career and cover design ===

sentences: Janjetov designed the album artwork for Heroina along with artwork for a number of other Yugoslav acts, including Oktobar 1864, Viktorija, Angel's Breath, but also for international world music acts, like Zuco 103, Konono Nº1, Bebel Gilberto, Celso Fonseca, Tartit, Taraf de Haïdouks, Mahala Raï Banda, Kasai Allstars, Kočani Orkestar and other acts.
